Sentencas: The microstructural morphology of solid oxide fuel cell electrodes has been noted to impact electrode performance, particularly with respect to charge transfer.
Titulo: Two-dimensional charge transfer and space charge effects in extended surface solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: Drawing on thermal fin analysis, an analytical modeling concept has been applied to charge transport within the SOFC electrode microstructure.
Titulo: Two-dimensional charge transfer and space charge effects in extended surface solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: This approach has the ability to account for variable cross-section solid geometry and replicates experimentally observed behavior related to SOFC electrode sintering quality.
Titulo: Two-dimensional charge transfer and space charge effects in extended surface solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: Microstructural geometries simulated by periodic structures composed of iterated base units with variable cross-section are investigated using two approaches: an axisymmetric one-dimensional analytical model and an axisymmetric two-dimensional finite element model.
Titulo: Two-dimensional charge transfer and space charge effects in extended surface solid oxide fuel cell electrodes

Sentencas: The one-dimensional analytical approach can account for the role of microstructural geometry without space charge effects that arise at particle contacts within the microstructure.

Sentencas: The finite element model has been developed to enable consideration of the effects of two-dimensional transport and space charge regions near particle contact points.

Sentencas: This more detailed model is used to benchmark the one-dimensional axisymmetric approach.
